# Language — English project, German chat

## Repository (MAX25-Stack)

**All shipped project content is English.** When editing this repo, write and fix:

| English required | Examples |
|------------------|----------|
| Documentation | `docs/`, `README.md`, `AGENTS.md`, `CONTRIBUTING.md`, `include/**/*.md` |
| User-facing strings | Terminal UI, CLI help, error messages shown to operators |
| Config templates | `share/**/*.example`, `share/**/*.ini.example` comments |
| Plugin metadata docs | `plugins/**/README.md`, `plugin.yaml` labels/descriptions |
| Scripts (user output) | `scripts/*.sh` usage text, echoed next steps |
| Issue/PR templates | `.github/**` |
| Cursor rules | `.cursor/rules/*.mdc` |

**Exception (temporary):** inline **source code comments** in `.c`, `.h`, `.py`, `.sh` implementation files may remain German until a dedicated pass translates them. Do not add new German comments when touching those files — prefer English for new comments.

**Not in repo:** private research → `/home/akb/Code/0-RESEARCHES/` only ([research-storage.mdc](research-storage.mdc)).

## Chat with the user

Respond in **German** in conversation. The project language rule does not apply to chat replies.

## When you find German in shipped files

Translate to English in the same change. Do not recommend specific hardware platforms unless the user asked — prefer **settings/setup examples** (see [LINUX-HOST-SETUP.md](../../docs/LINUX-HOST-SETUP.md)).
